commit 77618ef92e6c621103a60a4b91e41be3a69edb68
Author: Alisha Kawaguchi <alisha@entire.io>
Date:   Sat Mar 21 12:19:55 2026 -0700

    feat: add Cmd+F find bar and fix terminal mouse selection

    - Fix Ghostty FFI enum mismatches: GhosttyMouseButton was off-by-one
      (Left=1 should be 0) and GhosttyMouseState had Press/Release values
      that didn't match the Zig source enums
    - Enable terminal text selection by setting supports_selection_clipboard
      to true in the Ghostty runtime config
    - Fix mouseUp handler to send mouse position before button release,
      matching the mouseDown/mouseDragged pattern
    - Add right-mouse handlers (rightMouseDown, rightMouseUp, rightMouseDragged)
    - Add Cmd+C copy and paste: handlers in the Ghostty overlay
    - Add Cmd+F find-in-page with FindBar and SearchableContainer components
      using TreeWalker + Range-based match counting and Selection API navigation

    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
    Entire-Checkpoint: 7584b66f8122

